WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:08.170 --> 00:00:09.780
 RER A is changing. 

00:00:11.040 --> 00:00:15.140
 On the RER A, to accompany the increase of the traffic and the arrival 

00:00:15.140 --> 00:00:18.580
 new trains at 2 levels, the tracks will be completely replaced. 

00:00:19.830 --> 00:00:23.630
 The RER A will be closed between the Defense and Auber of July 25 

00:00:23.630 --> 00:00:24.910
 as of August 23, 2015 included. 

00:00:25.150 --> 00:00:29.510
 To facilitate the movement of travelers in their new 

00:00:29.510 --> 00:00:33.410
 itineraries, the capacity of the metro and tram lines 

00:00:33.410 --> 00:00:34.810
 more solicited will be increased. 

00:00:36.520 --> 00:00:39.020
 Additional buses will also be offered. 

00:00:39.860 --> 00:00:44.280
 To help you anticipate the closure, RATP puts your 

00:00:44.280 --> 00:00:47.820
 available on its website a simulator of routes. 

00:00:48.880 --> 00:00:49.500
 But how does it work ? 

00:00:49.600 --> 00:00:54.210
 It is very simple. Just fill in your departure locations 

00:00:54.210 --> 00:00:56.720
 and arrival, the day of your trip, its time slot, 

00:00:58.900 --> 00:00:59.760
 the preferred mode of transportation. 

00:01:00.740 --> 00:01:02.310
 A walk option is also available. 

00:01:02.860 --> 00:01:05.460
 Remember that a few more steps can be synonymous with correspondence 

00:01:05.460 --> 00:01:08.420
 in less. All you have to do is click on Search for 

00:01:08.420 --> 00:01:11.490
 get your route. The additional journey time 

00:01:11.490 --> 00:01:14.460
 Estimate is shown in relation to your usual route. 

00:01:15.280 --> 00:01:18.900
 This new tool takes into account the closures of RER A and the 

00:01:18.900 --> 00:01:22.660
 RER C, the affluence in the big poles or the lines 

00:01:22.660 --> 00:01:26.440
 subway or bus that could be very busy during peak hours. 

00:01:27.200 --> 00:01:30.680
 The route simulator allows you to determine right now 

00:01:30.680 --> 00:01:32.890
 the route best suited to your situation. 

00:01:33.750 --> 00:01:36.990
 To try for yourself and to know everything about the work, 

00:01:37.570 --> 00:01:39.690
 go now to RATP.FR, 

00:01:39.770 --> 00:01:43.960
 you will know what to do when the work begins. 

00:01:44.700 --> 00:01:47.810
 And do not forget, the important thing is to anticipate. 

00:01:49.230 --> 00:01:51.940
 The renewal of the lines of the RER line A is a project 

00:01:51.940 --> 00:01:55.280
 unprecedented, which mobilizes all of RATP's business lines. 

00:01:56.390 --> 00:02:01.040
 RATP thanks all travelers for their patience and understanding. 

